    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1560"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1560">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/88.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to telegraphic instructions from the
                    Department and my telegraphic reply thereto, I now have the honor to quote the
                    English translation of a reply from the Minister of Foreign Relations of the
                    Constitutionalist Government relative to the reported execution of two Christian
                    Brothers and the imprisonment of eleven others. Secretary Fabela in his reply
                    says: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Your courteous note of the 21st ult. was read with much interest by the
                            First Chief of the Constitutionalist Army. In reply, I beg to advise
                            that according to reports made by General Villa he did not order the
                            execution of the two Christian Brothers in Zacatecas, nor the
                            imprisonment of eleven others as reported, but he did order their
                            expulsion.</p>
                        <p>I repeat the assurances of my distinguished consideration, etc.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Isiueo Fabela</hi>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Philip C. Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
